Content:
It depends on the compactness of the code. If it's a large function, I try to avoid it, but 100% adherence to "one entry, one exit" kind of misses the spirit of the idiom. Something like:<p><pre><code>    if (condition)
      return true;
    return false;
</code></pre>
is no less readable and sometimes more intuitive than the equivalent<p><pre><code>    bool x = false;
    if (condition)
      x = true;
    return x;</code></pre>
